reviews.review_text:
Awesome place to have authentic Telugu food here. Wasn't expecting this in Goa. Happy to be here for the next time veg food options.
Prawns fry was lip smacking.
But they closed the counter bit early like 10:45 PM is the last order time so kindly make note of it.
Overall nice place to be with family n friends.

We were of 4 members from hyderabad and we got shocked to see the quantity of chicken served for rs350 rs450 which is way less than one can imagine. The gongura chicken pulav had oil overflowing. I understand gongura takes bit more oil than other leaves, but there are better ways to reduce oil. Spl Biryani was not that great for rs450 as per these reviews. There is no point of selling dishes at this price when there is no value added to them. Just because there are less andhra cousin options in goa doesn't mean it will never have. Please improve the quantity, lessen the price and oil. We wont come here again and will not recommend anyone. Makes me wonder if these reviews are real. We left utterly dissapointed and money wasted with half filled stomach. I suggest you all going to mana andhra ruchulu in calangute which is by far affordable and real.

Update: reply to owner -
The reply shows your audacity. I have paid for the food you served us and you expect not to give any feedback? I would have surely shared this feedback if you had asked us on spot about the food. Hence I am recording it here. Grow up and learn to take a feedback amd improve yourself instead of asking me not to come again. Moreover I have already mentioned i wont come already.

All my reviews are my personal genuine feelings for what I have enjoyed or disliked (unlike the fake ones here). If you cant handle such reviews, better unlist yourself from Google maps. It will help genuine people like us to avoid places like this. I guess its high time to see trend of your reviews/feedback rather than checking the trend of your customer's timeline.

I have updated 2 stars from 1 star just to spread some positivity.
The food was awesome. It was literally feeling like I was having my home food. Spice level is also less. Overall food and ambience is awesome.

description:
### Trails Of Taste¬Æ - A Culinary Journey into Authentic Andhra Cuisine in Anjuna

With a remarkable rating of 4.6 from a robust 2,681 reviews, **Trails Of Taste¬Æ (TOT)** stands out as a gem for food lovers in Anjuna, Goa, specializing in authentic Andhra cuisine. Popularly tagged with specialties such as "kodi" (41 mentions), "songs" (31), "chicken pulao" (28), and "gongura chicken" (28), this restaurant promises a vibrant culinary experience that brings the flavors of Andhra to the coastal paradise.

### Ambiance & Design

Stepping into **Trails Of Taste**, you're greeted by a warm, inviting atmosphere that strikes a balance between contemporary design and traditional charm. The interior is decorated with a mix of rustic and modern elements, which can be gleaned from customer photos showcasing wooden furnishings contrasted with colorful Andhra artwork. Warm lighting adds a cozy touch, making it an ideal setting for family gatherings or friendly get-togethers. From upbeat playlists featuring local tunes to the chatter of satisfied diners, the ambiance exudes a lively yet relaxed vibe.

### Menu & Culinary Experience

The culinary offerings at Trails Of Taste are a heartfelt homage to the diverse flavors of Andhra Pradesh. Signature dishes like the **Gongura Chicken Pulav** and **Chicken Pulao** are frequently highlighted in reviews, with one guest exclaiming, "It felt like I was having my home food." Diners can anticipate generous portions, although there have been mixed feelings about the amount served. The presentation is vibrant and enticing, with each dish adorned with fresh herbs and spices that not only tantalize the palate but also delight the eyes. Additionally, vegan and vegetarian options are notable, making the menu inclusive for all diners.

### Customer Experience & Service

While many reviews commend the friendly nature of the staff and the warm service at TOT, a few experiences tell a contrasting story. One guest expressed disappointment over the portion sizes for the prices charged, suggesting that value could be improved. Nevertheless, the overall sentiment leans positive, with diners appreciating the genuine enthusiasm that staff display towards the food they serve. Patrons are advised to note the early closing times, with the last orders being taken by 10:45 PM, so as not to be caught off guard.

### Popularity & Reviews

Social media buzz and word-of-mouth have significantly contributed to the restaurant's popularity, further affirmed by the good reviews from patrons who appreciate the quality and authenticity of the food. Although criticisms regarding portion sizes and prices have surfaced, the restaurant appears to maintain a core clientele that values its unique offerings in a region lacking in authentic Andhra cuisine options. 

### Utilizing Visual Content

The engaging visual content shared by diners adds another layer to the allure of Trails Of Taste. Pictures of the vibrant dishes, such as the striking **Prawns Fry** and colorful **Gongura Chicken**, illustrate not just the food but the love and intricacy involved in their preparation. These photos help potential customers visualize the experience waiting for them.

In summary, **Trails Of Taste** in Anjuna is a destination that encapsulates the essence of Andhra cuisine, drawing both locals and tourists looking to indulge in authentic dishes. Whether you're here for the flavorful food or the vibrant ambiance, this restaurant presents an experience that beckons you to come back for more.
